Here is Functional Requirements Documentation (FR-01 to FR-n) with Acceptance Criteria for your Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection, written in a clear SRS-style format that examiners usually expect.
Functional Requirements Documentation
Project: Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection
FR-01: User Registration and Account Setup
Description:
The system shall allow passengers to register and create an account using a mobile application or smart card by providing basic personal and payment details.
Acceptance Criteria:

User can successfully create an account with valid details
System validates user information
Account is created and stored securely
Error message is displayed for invalid or incomplete inputs
FR-02: Wallet / Bank Account Linking
Description:
The system shall allow users to link a digital wallet or bank account to enable fare payments.
Acceptance Criteria:

User can link a valid payment method
System securely stores payment credentials
Confirmation is shown after successful linking
Linking fails gracefully for invalid payment details
FR-03: Fare Payment Using Tap
Description:
The system shall allow passengers to pay bus fare by tapping an NFC-enabled device on the fare reader.
Acceptance Criteria:

Fare reader detects NFC device successfully
Correct fare is deducted from the user account
Transaction completes within acceptable time
System rejects payment if balance is insufficient
FR-04: Transaction Authentication and Security
Description:
The system shall authenticate each transaction using secure methods such as encryption and tokenization.
Acceptance Criteria:

All transactions are encrypted
No sensitive payment data is exposed
Unauthorized access attempts are blocked
System logs security-related events
FR-05: Payment Confirmation Notification
Description:
The system shall provide instant confirmation of payment to passengers and bus conductors.
Acceptance Criteria:

Visual or audio confirmation is displayed on the fare reader
Transaction status is shown to the conductor
User receives confirmation via mobile app or display
Failed transactions generate appropriate alerts
FR-06: Transaction Logging and History
Description:
The system shall record all fare transactions for future reference and auditing.
Acceptance Criteria:

Each transaction is logged with date, time, and amount
Users can view transaction history
Transport authority can access aggregated records
Logs are stored securely
FR-07: Fare Verification for Conductors
Description:
The system shall allow conductors to verify passenger payment status.
Acceptance Criteria:

Conductor can view real-time transaction status
System displays valid/invalid payment clearly
Verification does not delay boarding
FR-08: Backend Monitoring and Reporting
Description:
The system shall provide backend tools for transport authorities to monitor operations and generate reports.
Acceptance Criteria:

Revenue reports can be generated
Transaction summaries are available
Data is accurate and up to date
Authorized users only can access reports
FR-09: Error Handling and Alerts
Description:
The system shall handle errors such as failed transactions or device issues and notify relevant users.
Acceptance Criteria:

System displays meaningful error messages
Failed transactions do not deduct fare
Maintenance alerts are generated for device failures
FR-10: System Maintenance and Updates
Description:
The system shall support basic maintenance and software updates without disrupting operations.
Acceptance Criteria:

Updates can be deployed securely
System resumes normal operation after update
No loss of transaction data occurs
Summary
These functional requirements define the core capabilities of the Tap and Pay system and ensure secure, efficient, and user-friendly bus fare collection. Acceptance criteria provide measurable conditions to validate successful implementation.
