Non-Functional Requirements Documentation
Project: Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection
NFR-01: Performance
Description:
The system shall process fare payment transactions quickly to avoid delays during passenger boarding.
Acceptance Criteria:

Transaction processing time shall not exceed 2 seconds per tap
System shall support multiple transactions during peak hours
No noticeable lag in payment confirmation
NFR-02: Security
Description:
The system shall ensure secure handling of all payment transactions and user data.
Acceptance Criteria:

All transactions shall be encrypted
Sensitive user data shall not be stored in plain text
Unauthorized access attempts shall be prevented
System shall comply with digital payment security standards
NFR-03: Reliability and Availability
Description:
The system shall be reliable and available for continuous bus operations.
Acceptance Criteria:

System availability shall be at least 99% uptime
Transactions shall not be lost during system failures
System shall recover automatically after temporary failures
NFR-04: Usability
Description:
The system shall be easy to use for passengers and bus staff with minimal training.
Acceptance Criteria:

User interface shall be simple and intuitive
Passengers can complete payment with a single tap
Conductors can verify payments easily
Minimal training is required for operation
Summary
These non-functional requirements define the quality attributes of the Tap and Pay system, ensuring it is fast, secure, reliable, and user-friendly for public bus transportation.
