Appendix B: Brief Use Case Explanation (Optional but Recommended)
The Passenger interacts with the system to register, link a payment method, and pay the bus fare using a tap-based NFC mechanism. Upon successful payment, the passenger receives instant confirmation and can later view transaction history. The Bus Conductor verifies payment status in real time to ensure valid fare collection. The Transport Authority monitors system performance and generates revenue and usage reports. The Payment Gateway processes and authorizes all financial transactions securely.
