Here‚Äôs a Glossary tailored for your Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection project. This is written in a professional style suitable for SRS appendices or reports.
Project Glossary
Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection
Term	Definition
NFC (Near Field Communication)	A short-range wireless communication technology that allows devices to exchange information when in close proximity, used for contactless payments.
Tap and Pay	A digital payment method that allows users to complete transactions by tapping an NFC-enabled device or card on a reader.
Fare Reader	A device installed in buses to read NFC devices or smart cards and process fare payments.
Passenger	A person using the bus transportation system who pays fare using the Tap and Pay system.
Bus Conductor	A staff member who verifies payment status and assists passengers during boarding.
Transport Authority	The organization responsible for managing bus operations, revenue collection, and system monitoring.
Payment Gateway	A third-party service that securely processes digital payment transactions between passengers and banks.
Digital Wallet	An electronic account that stores payment information and allows users to pay digitally.
Tokenization	A security technique that replaces sensitive payment data with a unique token during transactions.
Encryption	The process of encoding data to prevent unauthorized access during transmission or storage.
Transaction History	A record of all payments made by a passenger, including date, time, and amount.
Authentication	The process of verifying a user or transaction for security purposes, often using PINs, passwords, or biometrics.
Backend Server	The central system that processes transactions, stores data, and communicates with payment gateways and transport authority systems.
Uptime	The period during which the system is operational and available for users.
Error Handling	The process by which the system manages failed transactions, device issues, or other operational errors.
Contactless Payment	A payment method that does not require physical contact, typically using NFC-enabled devices or cards.
