Project Charter
Project Title: Tap and Pay System for Contactless Bus Fare Collection
Project Start Date: [Insert Start Date]
Projected End Date: [Insert End Date]
Project Manager: [Insert Name]
Project Sponsor: [Insert Transport Authority / Department]
Project Team: [Insert Team Members Names & Roles]

1. Project Purpose and Justification
The purpose of this project is to develop a secure, fast, and contactless payment system for bus fare collection. Traditional cash and card-based methods cause long queues, boarding delays, and revenue management challenges. The Tap and Pay system will improve operational efficiency, reduce cash handling, and enhance passenger convenience by enabling NFC-enabled devices or smart cards for fare payments. This system will also ensure secure transactions, real-time fare validation, and transparent revenue reporting for transport authorities.
2. Objectives
Implement a contactless fare payment system for buses
Enable passengers to pay fare via smartphones, smart cards, or wearables
Ensure secure, encrypted, and tokenized transactions
Provide real-time payment confirmation to passengers and bus staff
Generate transaction logs and revenue reports for transport authorities
Minimize boarding delays and improve commuter experience
3. Scope
In-Scope
User registration and account setup
Wallet or bank account linking
Tap-to-pay fare system
Real-time payment confirmation
Payment verification for bus conductors
Transaction logging and history
Backend monitoring and report generation
Basic system maintenance and error handling
Out-of-Scope
Cash-based transactions and manual ticketing
Integration with other transport modes (metro, taxis)
Dynamic fare pricing or advanced analytics
Loyalty programs, rewards, or third-party advertisements
Customer support call centers, refunds, or dispute management
4. Stakeholders
Primary Stakeholders: Passengers, Bus Conductors, Bus Drivers, Transport Authority / Bus Operators
Secondary Stakeholders: Government / Regulatory Authorities, Banks / Payment Service Providers, System Developers, Hardware Vendors, Maintenance & Security Teams
5. Deliverables
Tap and Pay system software (mobile app & backend)
NFC fare readers integrated in buses
User registration and wallet/payment integration
Transaction logging and reporting system
Documentation: SRS, use case diagrams, stakeholder analysis, project glossary
6. Milestones
Milestone	Target Date	Deliverable
Project Initiation	[Date]	Project Charter Approval
Requirement Gathering	[Date]	SRS Documentation
System Design	[Date]	Architecture & Use Case Diagrams
Implementation	[Date]	Mobile App & Backend Development
Testing	[Date]	Functional & Security Testing
Deployment	[Date]	Go-Live on Pilot Buses
Project Closure	[Date]	Final Report & Documentation
7. Assumptions
Passengers will have NFC-enabled devices or smart cards
Reliable network connectivity is available in buses
Payment gateways are operational and secure
Transport authority provides access to bus infrastructure for installation
8. Constraints
Budget limitations for hardware and system deployment
Time constraints for development and testing
Compliance with government and digital payment regulations
Limited compatibility with legacy bus fare systems
9. Risks
Hardware failure or NFC reader malfunction
Insufficient user adoption or passenger resistance
Network outages causing transaction delays
Security vulnerabilities and potential fraud
